http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 16 Oct 2018
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2018; 31(42) [edited]
<www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=28273>


Equine influenza, Ecuador
-------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 16 Oct 2018 from Dr. Patricio Ramiro Garcia Villamarin, Executive Director, Agencia de Regulacion y Control Fito y Zoosanitario - Agrocalidad, Ministerio de Agricultura y Ganaderia, Quito, Ecuador,

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 10 Sep 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 17 Sep 2018
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease in the country
Causal agent: equine influenza virus
Serotype: not typed
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (10)
[The 10 outbreaks of equine influenza occurred in the following departments: Pichincha (7), Imbabura (1), Chimborazo (1), Santo Domingo de los Tsachilas (1). See details of each outbreak at the source URL above. - Mod.CRD]

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 10
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Equidae / 432 / 111 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 25.69 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: Following an equestrian event where were concentrated animals dedicated to leisure activities, notifications consistent with respiratory signs were received and allowed to determine, during clinical inspection and via laboratory tests, that it was equine influenza. As a result, holding events in which equines would be concentrated has been prohibited across the whole national territory.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; quarantine; disinfection; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak (s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Animal Health Diagnostic (National laboratory) / Equidae / competitive ELISA (c-ELISA) / 11 Sep 2018 / positive
Animal Health Diagnostic (National laboratory) / Equidae / real-time PCR / 17 Sep 2018 / positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

